The 500-bed isolation and quarantine field hospital at Nasrec has been closed. Health officials say the resources used will be redirected to alternative facilities to build up capacity in case of a third wave. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Health Department has confirmed the Nasrec field hospital is officially closed. The remaining patients have been moved to other facilities for observation and treatment. READ:Â Nasrec field hospital 'ready' for possible influx of COVID-19 patients The facility was decommissioned as there is currently no need for additional beds. Health officials say the resources used will be redirected to alternative facilities to build up capacity in case of a third wave.